ARDBEG SCO SMALT ARDBEG DAY 113.4|ARDBEG|WHISKY-SCOTCH|SINGLE MALT SCOTCH|TX||On the nose Ardbeg Day presents smoky notes of mint toffee, hints of banana, apple, dark chocolate, leather and cinnamon along with oily crushed peat and a hint of lime juice. With water there is roasted coffee, smoked almonds, smoked fruits. It has chewy, warming mouthfeel with flavors of soot, coal tar soap, aniseed, leather and some distant herbal notes. The palate also boasts notes of sweet, maple-cured bacon, creamy coffee, salted cashew nuts, and delicate, tangy citrus. The finish is long and gentle, revealing soft, creamy vanilla, milk chocolate, and a malty, biscuit-like, barley base.

Big flavors have always been the cornerstone of our prized Texas whiskies, and this one is no exception. Made grain-to-glass using traditional pot still distillation ensures a rich and viscous spirit that stands up to aging in new charred oak without losing its essence. Each dram is full of character and body, with an aromatic entry and soft finish, for an approachable yet memorable experience. The palate is sweet with honey, cream, candied nuts, leather, and sandalwood

CHARLES GOODNIGHT BBN SM BATCH 115|CHARLES GOODNIGHT|WHISKEY-AMERICAN|BOURBON|TX||The nose begins with tree fruits - apricots, peaches, and nectarines, giving way to toasty oak notes of caramel, brown sugar, and sweet vanilla and just the memory of dark chocolate. On a third pass, notes of bright citrus-orange and lemon zest, with white pepper spice and just a hint of dried fruits-raisins and figs. The palate has a very viscous, almost creamy texture that dries out beautifully revealing caramel and honey sweetness, cream soda, toasted nuts, dark chocolate, and baking spices. A medium-long finish, with a lasting reminder of toasted hazelnuts and a touch of honey sweetness.

DAFTMILL SCO SM SUMMER 2006 12Y 92|DAFTMILL|WHISKY-SCOTCH|SINGLE MALT SCOTCH|TX||The nose opens with freshly baked Victoria sponge, curry leaves and cinder toffee, with tinned peaches and warm gorse flower developing with time in the glass. These notes continue onto the palate, but are joined by lemon zest, molten honey on toast, marmalade and vanilla pods, with wood polish and marzipan appearing on the back palate. On the finish, waves of honey and spicy oak linger, with fruit-salad chews appearing after a minute or so. This is an excellent dram for a warm summer's day.

With time, honeyed beeswax, sweet lemon candy, apricot jam, and hints of fresh cake dough come through. The palate balances the spicy oak with the fruitier distillate before giving way to notes of caramelized brown sugar, toffee and hints of and marzipan. Wood spice is dominant on the long finish, giving waves of warming cinnamon and dried ginger.

DOS TIRANOS MEZCAL 80|DOS TIRANOS|TEQUILA & AGAVE SPIRITS|MEZCAL|TX||Mezcal is the name for the family of alcoholic drinks distilled from Agave americana, known as Maguey in its native Mexico. It could be considered a kind of parent drink to Tequila, but is not exported to the same degree. An earlier alcoholic drink called Pulque had been made in Mexico from fermented agave, but the distillation process is unlikely to have been used before European arrival.The strong and smoky flavor of Mezcal comes from a cooking process that can last several days. This is done after harvest in an earthen oven or enclosed barrel that allows the flavor to develop over an extended period.

GAETANO CREME DE MENTHE GREEN 30|GAETANO|LIQUEUR|CREME DE MENTHE|TX|MINT|Gaetano Creme de Menthe Green is a mint-flavored liqueur. The taste is sweet and spearminty. Though very similar to Creme de Menthe White, Creme de Menthe Green is a bar staple commonly used for giving drinks an exotic, green appearance. Popular in classic drinks like the Grasshopper: equal parts Gaetano Creme de Menthe Green, Gaetano Creme de Cacao White and light cream. Other popular drinks made with Creme de Menthe Green include the Green Milkshake, Creme de Menthe Frappe and Mint Highball.
GAETANO CREME DE MENTHE GREEN 30LI|GAETANO|LIQUEUR|CREME DE MENTHE|TX|MINT|Gaetano Creme de Menthe Green is a mint-flavored liqueur. The taste is sweet and spearminty. GAETANO CURACAO BLUE 30 LI|GAETANO|LIQUEUR|CURACAO|TX|ORANGE|Gaetano Blue Curacao is a sweet blue liqueur distilled and flavored from the dried peels of bitter oranges. Curacao, the liqueur, was first invented by Dutch settlers on the island of Curacao. The origin of this liqueur has much to do with its popularity as an ingredient in mixed, tropical drinks. Blue Curacao is a bar staple among today's mixologists, commonly used for giving drinks an exotic, blue appearance. Popular cocktails made with Blue Curacao include the Blue Martini, Blue Margarita and Blue Mezcalita.
GAETANO CURACAO ORANGE 30|GAETANO|LIQUEUR|CURACAO|TX|ORANGE|Gaetano Orange Curacao is made from the peels of bitter oranges. It possesses a robust orange flavor and color and is ideal for creating an orange appearance in cocktails. The bitterness of the fruit mixes well with other bitter flavors, so Orange Curacao and tonic makes a very appetizing long drink. Other popular drinks include the East India Cocktail #2 or as an ingredient in a Cosmopolitan. Orange Curacao can also be used as an alternative to orange bitters.

A versatile and refreshing cocktail ingredient, Gaetano Melon Liqueur blends beautifully with fruit juices. Melon Liqueur is a bar staple among today's mixologists, commonly used for giving drinks an exotic, green appearance. GAETANO BANANA LIQ 30|GAETANO|LIQUEUR|FRUIT LIQUEUR|TX|BANANA|Gaetano Banana Liqueur is a sweet liqueur that remains true to the flavor of the fruit it is named for. Gaetano Banana Liqueur has many uses. It is well suited for shooters or tropical drinks and mixes well with coconut rum and vodka. It can also be added to any dessert recipe that calls for the taste of fresh bananas. Popular cocktails made with Banana Liqueur include the Banana Colada, Banana Daiquiri, Banana Rum Frappe and Chiquita Cocktail.

GAETANO PEPPERMINT SCHNAPPS 30 LI|GAETANO|LIQUEUR|SCHNAPPS|TX|PEPPERMINT|Gaetano Peppermint Schnapps is made from the oil of peppermint leaves. The color is crystal clear and the taste is cool and refreshing. This long-standing schnapps flavor is often consumed as a chilled shot and is also ideal as a digestif after a meal. Popular cocktails made with Peppermint Schnapps include the Peppermint Pattie, Girl Scout Cookie or served in hot chocolate.

Popular cocktails made with Sour Apple Schnapps include the Appletini, Apple Pie Martini, Jolly Rancher or as a chilled shot.

GAETANO TRIPLE SEC 30|GAETANO|LIQUEUR|TRIPLE SEC|TX|ORANGE|Gaetano Triple Sec is an orange liqueur that is sweet in taste, clear in color and made from all natural ingredients. The primary taste comes from the peels of California navel oranges. Triple Sec plays an essential role in margaritas but is also ideal for such popular drinks as the Sidecar, Long Island Iced Tea, Cosmopolitan and Kamikaze. Gaetano Triple Sec comes in a variety of different proof levels. 30o is the traditional proof for Triple Sec and is the most popular.

HENNESSY COG PRIVILEGE 80|HENNESSY|BRANDY-GRAPE|COGNAC|TX||The original V. S. O. P since 1817, meaning Very Superior Old Pale. Selected from 4 premier growing areas. Created in response to Prince Regent's request (later King George IV). On the nose, the first fragrances perceived are soft spices such as vanilla, clove and cinnamon. Then delicate toasted notes follow, arising from the maturation in oak barrels. On the palate, the natural balance of strength and smoothness creates a harmonious blend in which maturity combines with vigor. The structure is softened by fresh grape character. The highlight of tasting Hennessy V. S. O. P Privilege is the long-lasting finish, revealing the natural balance of the blend: testament to a superior cognac

LEPANTO BRANDY SOLERA GRAN RSV 80|LEPANTO|BRANDY-GRAPE|BRANDY DE JEREZ|TX||As a result of the high quality must used and the careful distillation this Brandy de Jerez is extremely delicate and elegant. It shows a bright topaz color with orange and golden tones. On the nose delicate aromas of caramel and vanilla, toasted notes and hints of wine due to the time spent in Sherry casks. On the palate dry and delicate with touches of toasted almonds from the Tio Pepe casks and raisins form the Matusalem casks. Ideal with a good cigar or a blue cheese such as Stilton.
LEPANTO BRANDY PX SOLERA GR RSV 80|LEPANTO|BRANDY-GRAPE|BRANDY DE JEREZ|TX||The influence of the time spent in old PX casks is evident in this Brandy de Jerez. Lepanto PX shows a dark amber color with mahogany tones. On the nose beautiful rich aromas of raisins and figs and notes of oak from the 15 years spent in cask. On the palate smooth and elegant with a sweet sensation. Ideal with a good cigar or cheese such as Gouda with a caramelized rim to bring out the Pedro Ximenez.
LEPANTO BRANDY O V SOLERA GR RSV80|LEPANTO|BRANDY-GRAPE|BRANDY DE JEREZ|TX||The 15 years spent in cask and the use of both ex Tio Pepe and ex Oloroso casks gives a complex and powerful yet elegant Brandy de Jerez. On the palate intense and extremely dry however maintaining an elegant smoothness. Ideal with a cigar or cured Manchego cheese.

LOCH LOMOND SCO SMALT 12YR 92|LOCH LOMOND|WHISKY-SCOTCH|SINGLE MALT SCOTCH|TX||Loch Lomond 12 Year has a deep fruity character of peach and pear layered with a vanilla sweetness and the characteristic hints of peat and smoke found in Loch Lomond whiskies.On the nose it presents crisp green apple, ripe pear and refreshing citrus lemon with background notes of golden cereal. The finish is medium length with gentle wood smoke and a lingering peaty tang.

LOCK STOCK&BARREL WSKY RYE 16Y 107|LOCK STOCK & BARREL|WHISKEY-AMERICAN|STRAIGHT RYE WHISKEY|TX||
LOCK STOCK&BARREL WSKY RYE 20Y 112|LOCK STOCK & BARREL|WHISKEY-AMERICAN|STRAIGHT RYE WHISKEY|TX||Because American whiskeys must be aged in new charred oak barrels to be labeled bourbon or rye, they run the risk of becoming over-oaked the longer they're aged. Lock, Stock & Barrel 20-Year avoids this result due to the cold climate, 3.5 barrel-char, and lack of toasting, providing a rich and robust, yet balanced, flavor. It features notes of warm spiced date cake, toffee, baking spice, dried apricot, cantaloupe, and peppery rye spice. Proof of 112 (56% ABV)

Color: Golden straw yellow with green highlights Bouquet: Vibrant intensity of green apple and citrus fruit; fresh mineral nuances and white flowers; elegant blonde notes of brioche and fresh nuts. Palate: Fresh white-fleshed fruits (pear, peach, apple) and vibrant citrus fruit brought to life with fine, lively bubbles and a bright finish.

Created in 1869, it embodies the unique Moet & Chandon style; a style that distinguishes itself by its bright fruitiness, seductive palate, and elegant maturity. Color: Golden straw yellow with green highlights Bouquet: Vibrant intensity of green apple and citrus fruit; fresh mineral nuances and white flowers; elegant blonde notes of brioche and fresh nuts. Palate: Fresh white-fleshed fruits (pear, peach, apple) and vibrant citrus fruit brought to life with fine, lively bubbles and a bright finish.

PUSSERS BRITISH NAVY RUM 15YR 84|PUSSER'S|RUM|NAVY RUM|TX||Pusser's is the original Navy Rum as served on board warships of Great Britain's Royal Navy for 330 years from about 1675 to 1970. It was a part of the life and times of Nelson and the old navy so aptly described in the novels of Patrick O'Brian! Pusser's 330 years of Liquid History has become the standard by which other dark rums are measured. Pusser's was never sold or offered to the public until 1979. Prior to this, if a rum connoisseur managed to obtain a tot or two, it was valued for a very special occasion.

WHISTLEPIG RYE BOSS HOG VII 105.8|WHISTLEPIG|WHISKEY-AMERICAN|STRAIGHT RYE WHISKEY|TX||On the nose it's intensely aromatic, with cinnamon sugar, allspice, and maple. The finish is everlasting with gobs of cinnamon, oak spice, and a gentle warmth demand another sip.
